  "text": "**Kubernetes metrics exposition pattern**: Kubernetes uses a custom metrics stability framework built on top of prometheus client_golang. The core abstraction is `KubeRegistry` (registry.go) which wraps `prometheus.Registry` with version-aware metric hiding. A global singleton `defaultRegistry` is created in `legacyregistry/registry.go`, which exposes `MustRegister`, `Register`, `Handler()`, and `HandlerWithReset()`. Components register metrics via `legacyregistry.MustRegister()` (e.g., kubelet metrics, proxy metrics, scheduler metrics, volume metrics). The `/metrics` HTTP endpoint is configured in `apiserver/pkg/server/routes/metrics.go` via `DefaultMetrics.Install()` which calls `legacyregistry.Handler()`. Individual binaries (kube-scheduler, kube-proxy, controller-manager, kubelet) each wire `/metrics` to `legacyregistry.Handler()` or `legacyregistry.HandlerWithReset()` in their respective server.go files. The `http.go` file provides `HandlerFor` and `HandlerWithReset` wrappers around `promhttp`.\n\n**Grafana metrics exposition pattern**: Grafana uses dependency injection (Wire) to provide a `prometheus.Registerer` and `prometheus.Gatherer`. `ProvideRegisterer()` in `service.go` delegates to `legacyregistry.Registerer()` (reusing the Kubernetes component-base registry). `ProvideGatherer()` creates a `multiRegistry` combining a k8s gatherer (with `grafana_` prefix wrapper) and `prometheus.DefaultGatherer`. Metrics are defined in `pkg/infra/metrics/metrics.go` (via `initMetricVars`) and `frontendmetrics.go` (via `initFrontendMetrics`), both called from `ProvideService`. Some services also use `prometheus.MustRegister` directly (e.g., sqlstore, secrets manager). The `/metrics` endpoint is served in two places: (1) `pkg/server/instrumentation_service.go` uses `promhttp.Handler()` on a dedicated instrumentation HTTP server, and (2) `pkg/api/http_server.go` uses `promhttp.HandlerFor(hs.promGatherer, ...)` on the main API server. Alert-related subsystems create isolated `prometheus.NewRegistry()` instances for per-tenant metrics.",
